{
  "name": "RPlog_Stalh_Meets_Joir",
  "title": "Two Cold Men at the Swoop Races",
  "summary": "In the spectator stands of the Black Krayt Swoop Arena, the imposing, black-clad Joir arrives alone to find his assigned seat beside a brooding man in blood-red, Stalh, whose dark eyes and cold demeanor mirror his own. When Stalh dismisses the circling swoops as a pity, the two strike up a guarded, fencing conversation laced with veiled menace and recognition. Stalh challenges Joir's ticket and needles him over the one-eyed Imperial Ambassador Tazecks who issued it, while boasting of his knowledge of all things recent and arcane and hinting that he acts only because 'He' expects it. Joir, a former personal guard of Palpatine unshaken by such threats, parries each barb with arrogant calm and turns Stalh's veiled threat back on him. As a swoop crashes below, the two men trade final cold declarations of loyalty and intent, each refusing to be cowed by the other.",
